
You are only updating access. Following are some descriptions and examples of different ways to use the access property in a description. Use these as a reference when updating access in the description.

## access
The access field contains information about how a user may access, use, or otherwise interact with the resource. It may describe the physical or digital object.

| Property | Definition | Value type | Repeatable |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| url | URLs where the resource may be accessed in full or part. | Object (Description model) | Yes |
| physicalLocation | Location of a physical version of the resource. Physical location types must be from the "access.physicalLocation" controlled list. | Object (Description model) | Yes |
| digitalLocation | Location of a digital version of the resource, such as a file path for a born digital resource. Digital location types must be from the "access.digitalLocation" controlled list. | Object (Description model) | Yes |
| accessContact | The library, organization, or person responsible for access to the resource. Access contact types must be from the "access.accessContact" controlled list. | Object (Description model) | Yes |
| digitalRepository | The digital repositories that hold the resource. Digital repository types must be from the "access.digitalRepository" controlled list. | Object (Description model) | Yes |
| note | Other information related to accessing the resource. Access notes must be from the "access.note" controlled list. | Object (Description model) | Yes |

### Location of physical object

The location of the physical object that the digital object represents, such as a shelf locator or box and folder number. Do not use this field for archival series or record group.

Physical location types must be from the "access.physicalLocation" controlled list.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "physicalLocation": [
        {
          "value": "SC1070",
          "type": "shelf locator"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

#### Location of born-digital object

The file path to the original of a born-digital object.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "digitalLocation": [
        {
          "value": "C:\\home\\photographs\\portraits\\san-francisco\\file.jpg"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

#### Access contact name

The name of the library, department, or individual responsible for the resource, i.e., who a user should talk to for more information about the object. Use an authorized form of the name and provide a URI if available.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "accessContact": [
        {
          "value": "Stanford University. Libraries. Department of Special Collections and University Archives",
          "source": {
            "code": "naf"
          },
          "uri": "http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/no2014019980"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

#### Access contact email

The email of the library, department, or individual responsible for the resource, i.e., who a user should talk to for more information about the object. Used primarily with self-deposit.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "accessContact": [
        {
          "value": "me@stanford.edu",
          "type": "email"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

#### Alternative URL

An additional URL where a copy of the resource may be found. If it is a different version of the resource, use relatedResource instead. Use the top-level purl property for the object purl rather than entering it here. A display label and/or a note may be added to provide additional context for the URL.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "url": [
        {
          "value": "https://swap.stanford.edu/20171107174354/https://www.le.ac.uk/english/em1060to1220/index.html",
          "displayLabel": "Archived website"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}


#### Access note

Information about how the user may access the physical or digital resource.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "note": [
        {
          "value": "Available to Stanford researchers only.",
          "type": "access restriction"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

#### Use and reproduction note

Information about how the user may reproduce or otherwise use the resource.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "note": [
        {
          "value": "Contact specialcollections@stanford.edu for information about allowed uses and reproduction of this resource.",
          "type": "use and reproduction"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

#### License note

Information about a Creative Commons or other license associated with the resource.

{
  "access": [
    {
      "note": [
        {
          "value": "CC BY",
          "type": "license",
          "source": {
            "value": "Creative Commons"
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
